import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression

# Prepare the data for linear regression
X = cleaned_df[['x']].values  # Predictor variable
y = cleaned_df['y'].values  # Response variable

# Create a linear regression model and fit it
model = LinearRegression()
model.fit(X, y)

# Make predictions
y_pred = model.predict(X)

# Calculate the coefficient of correlation (R)
correlation_coefficient = np.corrcoef(X.flatten(), y)[0, 1]

# Plot the original data points and the linear regression line
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
plt.scatter(X, y, color='blue', label='Data points')
plt.plot(X, y_pred, color='red', linewidth=2, label='Regression line')
plt.title('Linear Regression of Data')
plt.xlabel('x')
plt.ylabel('y')
plt.legend()
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()
